% Group theory: prove that the inverse of a product is the reverse product
% of inverses.  i(x * y) = i(y) * i(x)
%
% An easy equational problem, good as a quick smoke test for the online
% learning pipeline. Typically proved in ~20 given clauses, so online
% learning has just enough runway to begin adapting.
%
% Usage:
%   python3 -m pyladr.apps.prover9 --online-learning -f group_inverse_product.in

formulas(assumptions).
  e * x = x.
  x * e = x.
  i(x) * x = e.
  x * i(x) = e.
  (x * y) * z = x * (y * z).
end_of_list.

formulas(goals).
  i(a * b) = i(b) * i(a).
end_of_list.
